MANGUZI – The remains of a 12-year-old boy, who went missing on September 28, have been found in a plastic bag in Manguzi, northern KwaZulu-Natal. The boy's remains were found on September 30. KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said: "We can confirm that a case of murder was opened for investigation after a 12-year-old boy was found dead on September 30, 2016 at Thangeni area. He was reported missing on September 28. “(A) post-mortem will be conducted to determine the cause of death. Emanguzi police are investigating a case of murder,” Mbhele said. eNCA